result.formatted_address: Hongway Garden, 8 New Market St, Sheung Wan, Hong Kong
result.name: North Garden Restaurant (Sheung Wan)

reviews.text:
Not bad for a Chinese restaurant 
Portion of food for each dish was a bit small though...

Just an ordinary Cantonese style Chinese restaurant serving dim sum and other foods. The seating is comfortable and generally spacious. The food and dim sum served are up to standard but not outstanding. The service provided by the staff is acceptable. The prices are reasonable.
Nice restaurant,nice foods to eat👍

It doesn't get more real than this. Happy customers and happy servers. Good solid Cantonese foods. Go simple. We asked for soup of the day, sweet and sour pork, vegetable in claypot, crispy pork belly, and fried egg omelet with bitter mellon. NO CORKAGE CHARGE. Bring your own wines to enjoy boys! FREE FRUITS AND DESSERT! I asked for boiled red beans. The one in Central is closed. The one in Sheung Wan is just as good if not better. People have weddings and parties there too!
dim sum was  mediocre. tried this once only. the dimsum/seafood restaurant downstairs is much better.

result.formatted_address: 香港上環新街市街8號康威花園
result.name: 北園酒家 (上環店)

reviews.text: 好好👍👍👍
早茶點心可以，環境舒服，價格合理。
侍應不足，圍餐份量畧小，12位女士吃，碟碟清
地方虽然比别的酒楼埸所小些，但食物尚是可以滿足大家的喜爱，味道是不錯的，服务人员的素质尚算好的。虽只有一楼，但同样有客專用电梯，此是比較少見而难能可贵者，因为香港人，你要他们走楼梯上落去吃飯，购物，就一百個不原意了。此处有此等客專用电梯，是老板一個明智的抉择！
